---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const personSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "@id": "https://cranbournegaragedoorco.com.au/about/#founder",
  "name": "Catherine Salmon",
  "givenName": "Catherine",
  "familyName": "Salmon",
  "jobTitle": "Principal & Founder",
  "worksFor": {
    "@id": "https://cranbournegaragedoorco.com.au/#business"
  },
  "description": "Catherine Salmon is the principal and founder of Cranbourne Garage Door Co, with 18 years of garage door installs and repairs experience in Cranbourne."
};
---
<Layout
  title="About Cranbourne Garage Door Co — Catherine Salmon, principal & founder"
  description="Catherine Salmon runs Cranbourne Garage Door Co from Cranbourne — 18 years in garage door installs and repairs. AS 4505 compliant installer. Meet the principal who quotes your job and runs the crew."
  canonical="https://cranbournegaragedoorco.com.au/about/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(personSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">About Cranbourne Garage Door Co</span>
      <h1>Catherine Salmon &mdash; <span class="accent">18 years</span> in garage door installs and repairs across Cranbourne.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        The principal who quotes your job, runs the crew, and answers his own phone after hours.
        AS 4505 compliant installer.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">The principal</span>
      <h2>How Cranbourne Garage Door Co actually works.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width:65rem;">
        <p>Catherine is a Cranbourne local, a garage door installs and repairs principal of 18 years, and you'll find him at the Cranbourne community-Saturday more often than you'll find him in an office. The crew sponsors a junior sports team, the business is a registered training employer, and we run a working-bee for the local primary school every summer holidays. None of that is on the quote — but it does explain why our crew turns up. Cranbourne hires Cranbourne.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">The Cranbourne side of it.</h3>
        <p>
          Cranbourne is not a market we read about; it's the market we live in. Catherine
          runs the local school's working-bee roster &mdash; the kind of detail that doesn't fit on a quote but does explain why the
          crew is on time, why the price doesn't drift, and why we'd rather pass a job to a mate than
          do work in a suburb we don't know. Every quote we issue is from someone you can put a face to.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Credentials &amp; memberships.</h3>
        <ul style="margin-top:1rem;">
          <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">AS 4505 compliant installer</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Public liability + workmanship insurance current; certificates available on request.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Written, fixed-price quotes (no "from $X" range pricing).</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Same-person quoting and supervision &mdash; not a call-centre handoff.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="background:#f9fafb;">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">How we operate</span>
      <h2>What makes a Cranbourne Garage Door Co job different.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width:65rem;">
        <h3>One person, start to finish.</h3>
        <p>
          Catherine quotes the job and runs the crew that does the job. There is no
          handover, no junior estimator who lowballs the quote then upcharges on the day, and no
          third-party project manager who hasn't been on a job site in five years. If you ring at 7pm
          on a Wednesday, you get the person who's going to be on your property on Monday morning.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Written, fixed-price quotes.</h3>
        <p>
          Every quote we issue is all-inclusive &mdash; site assessment, weather risk, access risk,
          permit work if relevant. No "from $X" range pricing, no day-of-build surprise variations, no
          mid-job upsell. If a surprise lands on the dig that we did not allow for, it's our cost, not yours.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">A crew that stays the same.</h3>
        <p>
          The Cranbourne crew is the same five people it has been for four years. We don't sub work out
          to chase-cheap labour-hire crews, we don't put apprentices on a job without a registered
          tradesperson actively supervising, and we don't run a roster of fly-in workers. Continuity
          is what makes the work hold up at the 10-year mark.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="background:var(--ink);color:#fff;">
    <div class="section-inner" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2 style="color:#fff;">Talk to Catherine directly.</h2>
      <p style="opacity:0.85;max-width:50rem;margin:1rem auto 2rem;">
        Quotes are free, fixed-price and same-person. Phones go to Catherine between
        7am and 7pm; after hours leave a message and we'll call back the next morning.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a fixed quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
